<doc id="866353" wikidata="Q5446326" url="?curid=866353" title="Ansaldo armored car (1925)">
<text>The Ansaldo armored car was a prototype armored fighting vehicle built by Ansaldo in 1925, based on a Pavesi P4 heavy tractor.

==Design==
The prototype was armed with a 45 mm / 37 mm cannon in a turret. It had four diameter wheels with wide tyres. 
The engine was at the front behind a radiator protected by armour plates. Poor visibility and driving difficulties led to abandonment of the project.

